> 
> It is probably minor, but it would be nice if it didn't fail like that.
> If I'm building an RPM package with ddccontrol, I can probably fix it,
> but it would be nice to not have to fix anything.

It doesn't fail, it just tries to install BlueCurve theme icon (as the
guy who provided the icon has made a "standard" and a BlueCurve icon),
and if it can't,  the error is ignored and make continues. So I don't
think this will prevent you from making a RPM. If so, please tell me and
I'll try to change how this thing is handled.

Best regards,

Nicolas



